<br>
Rez, on occasion I use the 'reefer.'  I don't smoke cigarettes, I never have smoked cigarettes, and I don't plan on ever smoking cigarettes.  I think they're gross, it's not a huge thing, it's just not for me.<br>
<br>
I don't smoke weed to &quot;be cool.&quot;  I don't smoke just for the sake of smoking.  I smoke to get high, once I'm high, I stop smoking.  <br>
<br>
The reason I do this, on occasion, is because, well, it's a helluva lotta fun.  Now, I feel that if you resort to drugs or alchohol to *have* fun, then that is a problem.  If it's one of the things you do, occasionally -- like getting drunk -- then it's fine.  I believe *anything* is bad if you do it too much.  Drugs.  Alchohol.  Sex.  Eq.  Eating.  Sleeping. <br>
<br>
But in moderation?  Hell most things are fine.  Just play it smart, use your head, and don't abuse what you use.  God taht sounded like a commercial.  I'll give you a quick list of things that are so much more fun high, you wonder why you hadn't tried the stuff earlier =p<br>
<br>
1. Swimming<br>
2. Hot tubbing<br>
3. Snowboarding<br>
4. Walking around hehe<br>
5. Any of the above, while listening to ANY music<br>
6. Any music<br>
7. Snowball fights<br>
8. Just sitting and talking with friends<br>
9. Playing video games<br>
10. Reading a good book<br>
<br>
Any number of things, you get the idea.<br>
I had to leave and run some errands mid-post, and I lost my train of thought once I got back, so I'm just posting what I have.<br>
